    "In 1926 her <em>Art Through the Ages: An introduction to Its History and Significance</em> appeared, which she used in her courses.": [],
    "This innovative survey text brought her national recognition, and lectureships at the University of California at Los Angeles in 1927.": [],
    "The following year she lectured at her alma mater before returning to the SAIC.": [],
    "Gardner published an art appreciation text, <em>Understanding the Arts</em> in 1932, which was directed toward art educators.": [],
    "She was appointed full professor and the department chair in 1934.": [],
    "A second, expanded edition of <em>Art Through the Ages</em> appeared in 1936, and including section of modern art, which had been omitted in the earlier edition.": [],
